---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ContentSection from "@components/content/ContentSection.astro";
import ContentCard from "@components/content/ContentCard.astro";
import stats from "../../data/stats.json";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");
---

<BaseLayout>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section
    class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-600 via-blue-700 to-teal-600 py-20"
  >
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 bg-repeat opacity-10"
      style={`background-image: url('${base}/grid.svg')`}
    >
    </div>
    <div class="container relative mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6">PROJECT</h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-blue-100 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Collective Research Portal of Spanish Universities
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS INV.ES? -->
  <ContentSection
    background="white"
    maxWidth="wide"
    paddingY="small"
    backgroundImage="/project-collab-bg.png"
  >
    <ContentCard variant="highlighted" padding="large">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">WHAT IS INV.ES?</h2>
      <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          INV.es is the <span class="font-semibold text-blue-700"
            >gateway to Spanish scientific production</span
          >, a collaborative platform that unifies and makes visible the results
          of research carried out in public universities.
        </p>
        <p>
          It is an initiative promoted by the <span
            class="font-semibold text-slate-900"
            >Conference of Rectors of Spanish Universities (CRUE)</span
          > and developed by the <span class="font-semibold text-slate-900"
            >Dialnet Foundation</span
          >, which aims to create a shared, sustainable information system
          governed by the academic community itself.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ContentCard>
  </ContentSection>

  <!-- ORIGIN -->
  <ContentSection
    background="slate"
    maxWidth="wide"
    paddingY="small"
    backgroundImage="/project-origin-bg.png"
  >
    <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-8">
      <div
        class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 rounded-xl bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/20 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-lg"
      >
        <svg
          class="w-8 h-8"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            stroke-width="2"
            d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">ORIGIN</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-100 font-medium">
          Recovery, Transformation, and Resilience Plan
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <ContentCard padding="large">
      <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          INV.ES emerges within the framework of the Recovery, Transformation,
          and Resilience Plan, through the UniDigital program, promoted by the
          Ministry of Universities to advance the modernization and
          digitalization of the Spanish university system.
        </p>
        <p>
          The project is developed under Royal Decree 641/2021, which regulates
          the direct granting of subsidies to Spanish public universities for
          investment in digital infrastructures, technological developments, and
          collaborative inter-university projects of general interest to the
          university system.
        </p>
        <p>
          In this context, the University of La Rioja, as coordinating
          university, presented in November 2021 the proposal for the
          inter-university project Collective Research Portal of Spanish
          Universities (INV.ES). The project was conceived from its inception as
          a collaborative initiative, aligned with the objectives of UniDigital
          and oriented towards generating a shared, reusable, and sustainable
          solution.
        </p>
        <p>
          The technical management and development of the project have been
          undertaken by the Dialnet Foundation, which has made the Dialnet CRIS
          technology available to INV.ES, a consolidated infrastructure widely
          implemented in the university sector, guaranteeing interoperability,
          scalability, and utilization of the portal by the entire Spanish
          university system.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ContentCard>
  </ContentSection>

  <!-- A COLLABORATIVE PROJECT -->
  <ContentSection background="white" maxWidth="wide" paddingY="small">
    <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-8">
      <div
        class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-600 to-cyan-600 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-lg"
      >
        <svg
          class="w-8 h-8"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            stroke-width="2"
            d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"
          ></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">
          A COLLABORATIVE PROJECT
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 font-medium">
          Spanish public universities and Dialnet Foundation
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <ContentCard padding="large">
      <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          INV.ES is the result of collaboration between Spanish public
          universities, with the Dialnet Foundation as the entity responsible
          for technical management and technological development of the project.
        </p>
        <p>
          In addition to the University of La Rioja, participants in the
          creation included the University of Santiago de Compostela, University
          of Burgos, University of Salamanca, University of C치diz, University of
          La Laguna, Pablo de Olavide University, University of Vigo, University
          of Le칩n, University of Alcal치, University of A Coru침a, University of
          Valladolid, and the National Distance Education University (UNED).
        </p>
        <p>
          More public universities have joined these, reaching the <a
            href={`${base}/en/#universidades`}
            class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline font-semibold"
            >current {stats.universities}</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          The solution is based on Dialnet CRIS technology, a consolidated and
          widely implemented system that allows integrating data from multiple
          institutions, ensuring their quality and offering them homogeneously,
          without dependencies on proprietary software. This approach ensures
          scalability, interoperability, and utilization of the portal by the
          entire university system.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ContentCard>
  </ContentSection>

  <!-- OPEN SCIENCE -->
  <ContentSection
    background="slate"
    maxWidth="wide"
    paddingY="small"
    backgroundImage="/project-science-bg.png"
  >
    <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-8">
      <div
        class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 rounded-xl bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/20 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-lg"
      >
        <svg
          class="w-8 h-8"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            stroke-width="2"
            d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253"
          ></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">
          BOOSTING OPEN SCIENCE
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-100 font-medium">
          Transparency, accessibility and global collaboration
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <ContentCard variant="highlighted" padding="large">
      <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          INV.ES is conceived from its origin as an infrastructure aligned with
          the principles of open science, understood as a model that promotes
          transparency, free access to scientific knowledge, and the reuse of
          research results to maximize their social, academic, and economic
          impact.
        </p>
        <p>
          The portal facilitates unified access to the scientific production of
          Spanish public universities, prominently incorporating results
          available in open access and favoring their visibility and
          dissemination through a single consultation point. In this way, INV.ES
          contributes to reducing barriers to access to scientific information
          and to strengthening the role of universities as generators and
          transmitters of open knowledge.
        </p>
        <p>
          Furthermore, INV.ES promotes interoperability and reuse of scientific
          information, through the standardization of data from multiple
          institutions and the adoption of common information models. This
          approach facilitates the exploitation of data by researchers,
          universities, institutional leaders, and other agents of the science,
          technology, and innovation system.
        </p>
        <p>
          The portal also incorporates analysis and visualization tools that
          allow contextualizing research activity, identifying collaboration
          networks, and analyzing trends, contributing to greater transparency
          in the evaluation and monitoring of university research.
        </p>
        <p>
          In line with international commitments on open science, INV.ES offers
          an aggregated presentation of scientific production linked to the
          Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), highlighting the contribution of
          Spanish universities to major social, economic, and environmental
          challenges.
        </p>
        <p>
          Through this approach, INV.ES establishes itself as a strategic
          infrastructure for advancing towards a more open, accessible,
          collaborative, and impact-oriented research ecosystem, strengthening
          knowledge transfer and the social return on public investment in
          research.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ContentCard>
  </ContentSection>

  <!-- CHALLENGES -->
  <ContentSection
    background="white"
    maxWidth="wide"
    paddingY="small"
    backgroundImage="/project-origin-bg.png"
  >
    <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-8">
      <div
        class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 rounded-xl bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/20 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-lg"
      >
        <svg
          class="w-8 h-8"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            stroke-width="2"
            d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">CHALLENGES</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-100 font-medium">
          Strategic, technological, and organizational challenges
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <ContentCard padding="large">
      <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          The development of INV.ES has involved addressing a series of
          strategic, technological, and organizational challenges, derived both
          from its inter-university character and from its vocation to serve the
          entire Spanish university system.
        </p>
        <p>
          One of the main challenges is the integration of information from
          multiple universities, each with its own systems, organizational
          structures, and data models. To this end, INV.ES has worked on
          defining a shared common language, capable of harmonizing and
          standardizing scientific information, ensuring its coherence, quality,
          and comparability.
        </p>
        <p>
          Associated with this, the project addresses the challenge of data
          deduplication and consolidation, especially regarding publications,
          authors, research groups, and institutional affiliations. The correct
          identification of researchers and results is key to offering reliable
          information and enabling advanced and reusable analyses.
        </p>
        <p>
          Another relevant challenge is the development of a scalable and
          sustainable technological infrastructure, capable of growing
          progressively in number of institutions, data volume, and
          functionalities, without depending on proprietary solutions or
          limiting its adoption by new universities. INV.ES responds to this
          challenge by relying on consolidated technology such as Dialnet CRIS
          and a collaborative model of continuous evolution.
        </p>
        <p>
          INV.ES also faces the challenge of balancing the informative function
          with the management function, offering a portal that not only serves
          as a showcase for university research, but can also be integrated into
          the internal processes of universities and support data-driven
          decision-making.
        </p>
        <p>
          Likewise, the project faces the challenge of effectively promoting
          open science, incorporating open data sources, highlighting production
          in open access, and facilitating the reuse of information, while
          respecting the regulatory frameworks and institutional policies of
          each university.
        </p>
        <p>
          Finally, INV.ES addresses the challenge of long-term governance and
          sustainability, establishing a shared model among participating
          universities that guarantees the evolution of the portal, its
          maintenance, and its adaptation to new needs of the university system
          and the research ecosystem.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ContentCard>
  </ContentSection>

  <!-- IMPACT - Bento Grid -->
  <ContentSection background="gradient" maxWidth="wide">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">IMPACT</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        INV.ES has a significant impact at different levels of the university
        and research system, contributing to improving the visibility,
        efficiency, and social value of research activities developed at Spanish
        public universities.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Bento Grid Layout -->
    <div
      class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 auto-rows-auto"
    >
      <!-- Card 1: Visibility - Large -->
      <div
        class="md:col-span-2 bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow reveal"
      >
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-4">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-teal-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-md"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"></path>
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M2.458 12C3.732 7.943 7.523 5 12 5c4.478 0 8.268 2.943 9.542 7-1.274 4.057-5.064 7-9.542 7-4.477 0-8.268-2.943-9.542-7z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">
            Visibility and Outreach
          </h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          First, the project strengthens the visibility and outreach of
          university research by offering a single, aggregating access point to
          scientific production, researchers, research groups, and lines of work
          developed at different universities. This facilitates both national
          and international dissemination of knowledge and recognition of the
          role of universities in scientific and technological advancement.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2: Decision Making -->
      <div
        class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow reveal"
      >
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-4">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-500 to-pink-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-md"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">
            Institutional Decision-Making
          </h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          INV.ES also has a direct impact on institutional decision-making by
          providing indicators, analysis tools, and visualizations that allow
          universities and academic and management leaders to have reliable,
          updated, and comparable information. This approach favors more
          strategic, evidence-based research management aligned with
          institutional objectives and public policies.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3: Research Community -->
      <div
        class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow reveal"
      >
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-4">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500 to-emerald-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-md"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Research Community</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          From the perspective of the research community, INV.ES contributes to
          improving access to scientific information, identifying collaboration
          opportunities, and analyzing research networks and trends,
          facilitating a more connected and collaborative environment between
          researchers and universities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 4: Open Science - Large -->
      <div
        class="md:col-span-2 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-teal-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow reveal"
      >
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-4">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-teal-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-md"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">
            Promoting Open Science
          </h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          The portal also has a relevant impact in promoting open science by
          highlighting production in open access, favoring data reuse, and
          increasing transparency of research activity funded with public funds.
          In this sense, INV.ES contributes to maximizing the social return on
          public investment in research.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 5: Knowledge Transfer -->
      <div
        class="md:col-span-2 bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow reveal"
      >
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-4">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500 to-red-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-md"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M3.055 11H5a2 2 0 012 2v1a2 2 0 002 2 2 2 0 012 2v2.945M8 3.935V5.5A2.5 2.5 0 0010.5 8h.5a2 2 0 012 2 2 2 0 104 0 2 2 0 012-2h1.064M15 20.488V18a2 2 0 012-2h3.064M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">
            Knowledge Transfer and Social Impact
          </h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          INV.ES also strengthens knowledge transfer and social impact by making
          visible the contribution of university research to the Sustainable
          Development Goals (SDGs) and major social, economic, and environmental
          challenges. This perspective allows connecting scientific activity
          with society's needs and with national and international agendas.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 6: Structural Impact -->
      <div
        class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow reveal"
      >
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-4">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-500 to-purple-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white shadow-md"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Structural Impact</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          Finally, the project has a structural impact by consolidating a
          collaborative and sustainable model, based on shared, reusable, and
          scalable infrastructures, which strengthens inter-university
          cooperation and lays the foundations for the future evolution of the
          portal as a strategic node of the Spanish science, technology, and
          innovation system.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </ContentSection>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Smooth hover effects for Bento Grid cards */
  .grid > div {
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .grid > div:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
  }
</style>
